RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMA CARPE DIEM Hustled from outside draw and cleared to rail and lead, maintained position throughout, fended off two foes to outside down the lane, resolute in victory. SHACKEY'S LOVE Let outside rival clear and settled outside in a stalking position, three wide up the backstretch and moved squarely into contention three deep down the lane, grinded up ground late but just missed. CROSS EXAMINE Taken ahold of along rail and set up well off pace, progressed throughout run up backstretch inside and breached into the fray at the quarter pole, split pair of rivals at eighth pole and battled between, not enough. MY SON CHRIS Broke a touch slow and made up half of back pair throughout running, engaged four wide as the field approached the turn, made a faint threat which was ultimately mitigated by the continuing top trio. PIRATE MISCHIEF Pressed two wide in the opening stages, remained contentious until being adjoined by other rivals at the quarter pole, gave way without much fight.

ENTRY.NAME: Cross Examine
ENTRY.COMMENT: Taken ahold of, progressed into fray 1/4, split 1/8, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Pirate Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pressed 2w opening stages, adjoined by others 1/4, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Shackey's Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: Let rival clear, stlk 3w, settld outs, fought 3w strch, missed

ENTRY.NAME: My Son Chris
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke a touch slow, taken back, engaged 4w into turn, mitigated

ENTRY.NAME: Ima Carpe Diem
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled, cleared, maintained lead, fended off foes, resolute

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DeFazio Distaff S. RILLITO RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. No trials and no nomination. An entry fee of $250 to be paid at the time of entry. Preference by earnings in 2022 and 2023. Maidens are least preferred. Same owner entries must prefer a horse at the time o f entry. Weights: 3 years old .124 lbs., Older .126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED NOON RISING Stalked on rail opening stages, made steady middle move up the backstretch, loomed two wide approaching the quarter pole, engaged in battle from that point and fought through lane, lifted late to win. CHARMANT E Broke inwards, stalked on rail, overtook for the lead at the half-mile pole, joined by outside rival at the quarter pole, dueled throughout lane on inside, outfinished. QUEEN OF LOVE Tracked off the pace two deep, showed improvement at quarter pole, no better than third best. CLUBHOUSE SAINT Taken back to trail early, in three path on first turn, idled along backside, four wide bid on turn, mild headway down center of course gained a few placings past tiring rivals. PLATINUM GREEK Off pace on inner part of course, got out slightly into the first turn, never impressionable in running. LOVELY LOLA Tracked inside, asked at quarter pole, never improved. ALLIE'S PAL Sent hard to lead and battled on rail through opening stages, overtaken by gaining rival at three eighths pole, steadily faded from there to wire. WE ALL AGREE Broke sharply outwards, engaged and sent hard to duel for early lead, failed to corner into the first turn and ended up on outer rail by the time field reached the backstretch, taken out of contention from that point and taken care of all the way home.

ENTRY.NAME: Lovely Lola
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked inside, asked 1/4, never improved

ENTRY.NAME: Red Noon Rising
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid-pck rail, middle move, loomed 2w 1/4, fought outs, liftd late

ENTRY.NAME: Platinum Greek
ENTRY.COMMENT: Off pace inner, got out slightly first turn, never impressionable

ENTRY.NAME: Charmant E
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalked on rail, overtook 1/2, joined by rival 1/4, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Clubhouse Saint
ENTRY.COMMENT: Taken back last, 3p 1st turn, 4w bid turn, mild headway center

ENTRY.NAME: Allie's Pal
ENTRY.COMMENT: Sent hard, battled on rail, overtaken 3/8ths, steadily faded

ENTRY.NAME: Queen of Love
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked off pace 2 deep, improved 1/4, clear third best

ENTRY.NAME: We All Agree
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke outwards sharply, sent, blew first turn, out of contention

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY NOGUEZ Established rail in even line of three heading into first turn, astride with outside rival from three-quarter pole to seven-sixteenths pole, took clear command beyond then, dominated in hand. BRITE TAN Found herself between two rivals into the first turn, ran evenly with inside rival down stretch first time by, into backstretch dropped to a clear second at seven-sixteenths pole, sent along at the quarter pole, had nothing left. SHE'S MY RIDE Three wide into the first turn, dropped to a clear last as they went by the stands first time, asked at three-eighths pole, never contended.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Noguez
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail first, astride from 3/4 to 7/16, took command, in hand

ENTRY.NAME: Brite Tan
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w first, astride 2p with rival, second 7/16, sent 1/4, no left

ENTRY.NAME: She's My Ride
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, dropped to clear last 3/4, asked 3/8, never contended
